The Senate caucus of the All Progressives Congress (APC) will at 2:30 pm today meet with the National Leader of the party, Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu. The meeting was disclosed by the Senate President, Ahmad Lawan, in a letter he read during the start of plenary on Wednesday. Reading the letter, Lawan said, “there will be APC Senate caucus meeting with His Excellency, Senator Bola Ahmed Tinubu today, February 16, 2022.” The APC leader is billed to meet with the party’s caucus at the House of Representatives immediately after his meeting with the Senators. The meeting is part of efforts to galvanize support for his presidential ambition in the 2023 elections. The letter was signed by the Senate Leader, Senator Yahaya Abdullahi (Kebbi North).